1
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,540
=Fireworks=

2
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,860
=Episode 12=

3
00:00:20,679 --> 00:00:22,399
(How did Qiao Nian know about this?)

4
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:29,300
(Mr. Liu)

5
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,200
Hello?

6
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,000
Ms. Qiao.

7
00:00:33,039 --> 00:00:33,840
Yes, Mr. Liu?

8
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:35,600
What's wrong?

9
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,359
Is what they're saying in the news true?

10
00:00:37,679 --> 00:00:38,520
Oh, Mr. Liu,

11
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:39,280
it's like this.

12
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:41,359
What Qiao Nian said isn't true.
Don't trust her.

13
00:00:41,359 --> 00:00:42,719
We should hold off on our partnership.

14
00:00:42,719 --> 00:00:43,320
Mr. Liu.

15
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:44,799
- That's it.
- Wait.

16
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,439
Hello, Mr. Zhang?

17
00:00:50,439 --> 00:00:51,359
- Qiao Wenjun,
- Yes.

18
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,560
- the factory's forgery
- I can explain.

19
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,679
- is causing a huge stir.
- It's like this.

20
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:54,560
Solve it now!

21
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,520
Mr. Zhang, I...

22
00:00:59,759 --> 00:01:03,000
Qiao Nian, don't think
you've got me cornered like this.

23
00:01:08,079 --> 00:01:09,480
Nian.

24
00:01:20,599 --> 00:01:21,480
Nian.

25
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,159
Let's talk.

26
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:33,319
Nian, how have you been?

27
00:01:33,519 --> 00:01:35,079
You don't have to act.

28
00:01:35,599 --> 00:01:37,200
What did you

29
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:38,799
come here for today?

30
00:01:42,079 --> 00:01:43,480
My only purpose

31
00:01:44,319 --> 00:01:45,319
in seeing you today

32
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:48,200
is to seek your forgiveness.

33
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,560
Forgiveness?

34
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:58,040
What right
do you have for me to forgive you?

35
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:01,040
You know what you've done.

36
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:05,760
Nian, I know I was wrong.

37
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:09,599
I was trapped by obsession
and hatred before.

38
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,039
I thought Dad didn't appreciate me.

39
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:13,800
I wanted his approval.

40
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:17,639
I even put the pressure
of this family on Yiran.

41
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:20,479
That's why
she made the mistake and hurt you.

42
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,759
I'm really sorry.

43
00:02:25,439 --> 00:02:27,240
She's mentally unstable now.

44
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:30,120
She's been sent
to a psychiatric ward overseas.

45
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,719
I want to go be with her.

46
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:35,800
From now on,

47
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,439
I'll leave the company to you.

48
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,039
Oh.

49
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:42,560
To be exact,

50
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,599
it was always yours.

51
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,199
You want to give me the company?

52
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:52,800
There's no point in fighting like this.

53
00:02:53,439 --> 00:02:57,319
Plus, I've seen my own limitations.

54
00:02:58,039 --> 00:03:00,400
I have to admit,
your grandpa had good foresight.

55
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:04,400
Handing the company to you
is the right move.

56
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:09,280
So, you're reflecting on yourself?

57
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:15,879
Nian.

58
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:19,199
To tell you the truth,

59
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,400
I was there that day

60
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,639
in the basement.

61
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,479
I could've saved Dad.

62
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,759
But I was blinded by obsession.

63
00:03:31,719 --> 00:03:33,479
I chose to turn a blind eye.

64
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,199
That's how Dad
ended up dying in the fire.

65
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:40,759
You're admitting it?

66
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,560
Why did you do it?

67
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:48,759
I've always thought
Dad didn't approve of me

68
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,479
because I'm a woman.

69
00:03:51,599 --> 00:03:53,639
No matter how hard I tried,

70
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,080
it was never enough
compared to your dad.

71
00:03:56,919 --> 00:03:59,759
He ran off with your mom,
Xie Yunyi, back then.

72
00:03:59,879 --> 00:04:00,919
It was me.

73
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:03,080
I kept the company afloat.

74
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:06,800
But Dad wanted
to hand the company to you.

75
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:10,680
I once thought it was unfair.

76
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:13,439
You think I'll pity you
just because you said all this?

77
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:18,439
You keep saying
you kept the company afloat,

78
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:22,000
but what have you
been doing all these years?

79
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,240
Making huge profits.

80
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:25,399
Faking products.

81
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:28,780
It was right for Grandpa
not to give the company to you.

82
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,319
I realize my mistakes, Nian.

83
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:35,920
Please forgive me.

84
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,040
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:40,399
I really regret it.

86
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:43,959
I regret not saving Dad.

87
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,439
Will you forgive me?

88
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:46,519
Don't give me that.

89
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:48,120
Get up.

90
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,920
Get up!

91
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,600
Do you think I'm your only enemy?

92
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:15,120
Jiang Xiao.

93
00:05:15,199 --> 00:05:17,439
Jiang Xiao's been
obsessed with your mom.

94
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,879
He's just like me.

95
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:24,319
He'll do everything he can
to get noticed.

96
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:25,839
Don't you think

97
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:28,759
he had it all planned from the start?

98
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:32,800
He got his son
to approach you with a purpose.

99
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:38,439
Otherwise, how would your mom
just disappear like that?

100
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,399
And just when you were at your weakest,

101
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:45,480
Jiang Zechen
just so happened to show up.

102
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:47,480
What you said,

103
00:05:48,519 --> 00:05:49,759
whether it's true or not,

104
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,040
I'm going to investigate it.

105
00:05:54,199 --> 00:05:55,800
If you want to give up on Qiao Group,

106
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,800
shouldn't you show some sincerity?

107
00:06:11,319 --> 00:06:12,920
This is the stock transfer agreement.

108
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:16,720
(What is she up to now?)

109
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,680
After talking to you today,

110
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,680
I'll leave Qiao Group.

111
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,000
The Jiang family

112
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,120
is not as simple as you think.

113
00:06:50,319 --> 00:06:52,160
(This transfer agreement isn't stamped.)

114
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:53,600
(There's no fingerprint either.)

115
00:06:54,199 --> 00:06:55,399
(Does she think I'm a fool?)

116
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:13,040
Your family is known
for your stubbornness.

117
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,319
That stubbornness
has fooled a lot of women.

118
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,240
(Does she know something?)

119
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:33,000
What did she say to you?

120
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:36,000
She said she wants
to give Qiao Group to me.

121
00:07:37,839 --> 00:07:38,639
What?

122
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,560
You don't believe it either, do you?

123
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,360
She wouldn't be so kind.

124
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,759
This must be her delaying tactic.

125
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,199
It's time to end this game,

126
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,040
my dear niece.

127
00:08:03,839 --> 00:08:05,639
(The goods have
arrived at the destination.)

128
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,690
(The funds transfer
can be initiated at any time.)

129
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:37,559
You think getting my resignation letter
means you won?

130
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:45,120
Get ready for the ultimate gift
I'm sending you.

131
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:50,000
It's time for your exit.

132
00:08:55,280 --> 00:09:01,250
♪So many words unsaid,
the deeper we fall, the more we fear♪

133
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:09,130
♪Fate like a gamble,
locking us inside its game♪

134
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:12,970
♪Hearts at play, truth and lies,
who could ever know♪

135
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:16,770
♪Where this ends♪

136
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:24,050
♪I try to walk away,
yet still step into the fire♪

137
00:09:24,050 --> 00:09:28,380
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

138
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:31,500
♪Love turns into pain♪

139
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:35,690
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

140
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:39,330
♪Yet I still want you close♪

141
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:43,500
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

142
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,810
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

143
00:09:46,810 --> 00:09:51,380
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

144
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:57,690
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪

145
